install git for windows

// ref : http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6883760/git-for-windows-bashrc-or-equivalent-config-files-for-git-bash-shell
setup  ~/.bashrc 
~ is usually your C:\Users\<your user name> folder. Typing echo ~ in the git bash terminal will tell you what that folder is.

// ref : http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2114111/where-does-git-config-global-get-written-to
setup ~/.gitconfig
git config --global --edit should tell you the exact location no matter what kind of setup you have--just look at what file comes up in your editor.
